--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8eb9d9fa0ccbe1b4cbcd2a1d889b806b, type: 3}
  m_Name: FirstDayConvo02
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialogue
  conversationName: FirstDayMainConversation
  lines:
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Oh, please, don't look so horrified. You didn't think humans were the <i>only
      ones</i> who wanted to purchase goods sourced from other creatures, did you?
      Haha!
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: There are plenty of... <i>other</i> creatures in this world with money
      to spend-- and they all have a <i>monstrous</i> appetite for human material,
      heh heh.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: They come from far and wide to get their hands on the rare human products
      that are for sale at this hotel.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Whether they eat them, make potions with them, whatever-- it's not our
      concern. We just stock the shelves and make money.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: The types of goods we sell here are difficult to find on the... <i>public</i>
      markets, as I'm sure you can understand. This gives us an excellent business
      opportunity to fill the market gap.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Ah, I see all the color has drained from your cheeks... If you plan to
      pass out, please do it outside of work hours, on your own time. And don't bother
      trying to escape-- I can assure you, it won't work.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Now, I am indeed aware that you are human-- just like the unsuspecting
      guests who stay at this hotel; however, your position as my employee will prevent
      you from becoming an... <i>organ donor</i>, shall I say.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: So as long as you have this job, you have nothing to worry about!
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Regarding the guests you will be harvesting from, I have already taken
      the liberty of... <i>preparing</i> them. You will find them in their rooms,
      ready for harvesting.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: You don't have to worry about helping the guests with their 'departure'--
      I'll always handle that part before your shift starts.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Now, listen closely-- this hotel has a reputation to uphold for quality
      goods and excellent service; therefore, I have high standards.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: To ensure you are reaching those standards, you will have a <b>daily quota</b>
      for the amount of money you must make by the end of your shift.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: I must measure your job performance somehow, yes?
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Tonight, your <b>quota is (insert Quota here)</b>. I have given you a reasonable
      goal to reach for your first day; However, understand that the quota will be
      higher every day.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: I don't have to explain to you what will happen if you fail to reach quota,
      correct? A satisfactory job performance will give you more than just job security--
      it will lengthen your life, heh heh.
  repeatLine:
    speakerName: Randy
    line: Don't you have something else better to do?
